title: Sultan Haider of PML-N wins PP-20 Chakwal election
content:
ISLAMABAD, Feb 9 (APP): Sultan Haider Ali Khan of Pakistan Muslim League (N) has won the election for Punjab Assembly constituency PP-20 Chakwal-I by securing 52450 votes.
According to the unofficial result issued by the Returning Officer/ECP, the runner-up was Ali Nasir Khan, an independent candidate who bagged 43250 votes.
Votersâ€™ turnout remained 60.99 percent.
